28/12/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The government appointed Petko Sertov, incumbent secretary of the cabinet's Security Council, as head of Bulgaria's new State Agency for National Security on Thursday (December 27th). 
The new office would streamline the functions of the National Security Service, the military counter-intelligence and financial intelligence agencies, and will directly report to the prime minister.
In other news, the BiH Council of Ministers (CoM) appointed Mirko Lujic as the new head of the State Investigation and Protection Agency. 
The CoM also agreed that the new Agency for Protection of Personal Data should begin operations in April. 
(24 Chasa, Trud - 28/12/07; bTV, BNR, News.bg, RTRS, Fena - 27/12/07)
